<div id="content" class="backgrnd4"><div id="right"><div id="box1"><a href="iaai11.php"><img src="http://www.aaai.org/Conferences/AAAI/2011/Photos/sanfrancisco.jpg" alt="San Francisco" width="639" height="238" border="0" /></a></div><div id="box2"><h2 class="backgrnd7"><span class="text1">Please Join Us for IAAI-11!</span></h2><div class="content"><p>AAAI is delighted to announce that the Twenty-Third IAAI Conference on Artificial Intelligence will be held will be held in San Francisco, California at the Hyatt Regency San Francisco, from August 9&ndash;11, 2011.</p><p>The purpose of the IAAI-11 conference is to promote research in AI and scientific exchange among AI researchers, practitioners, scientists, and engineers in related disciplines.  On this page, you will find links to the wide variety of programs being held at IAAI-11 as they become available.</p><div class="hr1"><hr /></div><h3 class="text2"><a href="http://www.aaai.org/Conferences/AAAI/2011/aaai11speakers.php">The Exciting Slate of AAAI-11 / IAAI-11 Invited Speakers</a></h3><p><img src="http://www.aaai.org/Conferences/AAAI/2011/Photos/ferrucci.jpg" alt="David Ferrucci" width="65" height="75" class="img1" /><img src="http://www.aaai.org/Conferences/AAAI/2011/Photos/mantaras.jpg" alt="Ramon Lopez de Mantaras" width="66" height="75" class="img1" /><img src="http://www.aaai.org/Conferences/AAAI/2011/Photos/buelthoff.jpg" alt="Heinrich Buelthoff" width="54" height="75" class="img1" /><img src="http://www.aaai.org/Conferences/AAAI/2011/Photos/karahalios.jpg" alt="Karrie Karahalios" width="56" height="75" class="img1" /><img src="http://www.aaai.org/Conferences/AAAI/2011/Photos/kearns.jpg" alt="Michael Kearns" width="50" height="75" class="img1" /><img src="http://www.aaai.org/Conferences/AAAI/2011/Photos/konolige.jpg" alt="Kurt Konolige" width="63" height="75" class="img1" /><img src="http://www.aaai.org/Conferences/AAAI/2011/Photos/gunning.jpg" alt="David Gunning" width="54" height="75" class="img1" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;<br /><br /></p><p>AAAI-11 / IAAI-11 features an exciting slate of invited speakers, including keynote David Ferrucci (from IBM T. J. Watson Research Center), the 2011 Robert S. Engelmore Memorial Award Lecturer Ramon Lopez De Mantaras (from the Artificial Intelligence Research Institute and Spanish National Research Council), and invited speakers Heinrich H. Buelthoff (Max Planck Institute for Biological Cybernetics), Karrie Karahalios (University of Illinois), Michael Kearns (University of Pennsylvania), Kurt Konolige (Willow Garage, Inc and Stanford University), and David Gunning (Vulcan Inc.). <a href="http://www.aaai.org/Conferences/AAAI/2011/aaai11speakers.php">Details on these and the 25th anniversary panel!</a></p><div class="hr1"><hr /></div><h3 class="text2">The Conference Venue</h3><p>San Francisco is full of delights for every visitor. From the iconic Golden Gate bridge to world-class art galleries, science museums, and picturesque neighborhoods, the City takes pride in its unrivaled attractions and treasures. AAAI-11 will take near the foot of Market Street &mdash; a great starting point to explore the City's great ethnic and cultural diversity, its wide variety of shops, world-class restaurants, and theater. It's not too early be begin making your tentative plans now to join us in San Francisco! <a href="http://www.sfgov.org/site/visitor_index.asp">More&#8230;</a></p><div class="hr1"><hr /></div><!--<h3 class="text2">Submit a Paper to IAAI!</h3><p>We invite you to submit your paper to IAAI. <a href="http://www.aaai.org/Conferences/IAAI/2011/iaai11call.php">More&#8230;</a></p><div class="hr1"><hr /></div>--><h3 class="text2">Become a Sponsor of AAAI-11</h3><p>Your participation in the IAAI-11 / AAAI-11 Sponsor Program will give you instant visibility to a diverse group of AI professionals. <a href="http://www.aaai.org/Conferences/AAAI/2011/aaai11sponsorship.pdf">More&#8230;</a> </p><div class="hr1"><hr /></div><h3 class="text2">Exhibit at IAAI-11 / AAAI-11</h3><p>AAAI invites you to exhibit at AAAI-11/IAAI-11 &mdash; an excellent way to reach the leading scientists who are conducting groundbreaking research in artificial intelligence and the premier venue to reach this audience. <a href="http://www.aaai.org/Conferences/AAAI/2011/aaai11exhibits.php">More&#8230;</a></p><!--<h3 class="text2">Travel Information for International Visitors</h3><p>International travelers who are seeking to travel to the United States under the Visa Waiver Program are now subject to enhanced security requirements. All eligible travelers who wish to travel under the Visa Waiver Program must apply for authorization. <a href="https://esta.cbp.dhs.gov" rel="nofollow">More&#8230;</a></p><p><b>Timetable for Authors</b></p><p>December 1, 2009 &ndash; January 19, 2010: <a href="http://aaai.confmaster.net/pages/login.php?Conf=IAAI">Authors register on the IAAI web site</a><br />January 19, 2010: Electronic papers due<br />March 30, 2010: Camera-ready copy due at AAAI office</p><div class="hr1"><hr /></div>--><!--<h3 class="text2">IAAI Hotels</h3><p>AAAI has reserved blocks of rooms at the Sheraton Pasadena Hotel and Hilton Pasadena Hotel at reduced conference rates.<a href="http://www.aaai.org/Conferences/IAAI/2010/iaai10hotels.php">More&#8230;</a></p>--><p>We hope to see you in San Francisco!</p><!--<h3 class="text2"><a href="2010/iaai10committee.php">Program Committee</a></h3>--><div class="hr1"><hr /></div></div></div><div id="box3" class="backgrnd9">
